{{ if schedulerEnabled }}
## Task Scheduler

The Crego recipe enables the scheduler with `task_scheduler: gocron`. Set `task_scheduler: none` to generate the project without scheduled task executor code. The supported recipe values are `none` and `gocron`.

Runtime task configuration is loaded from the generated app config:

```yaml
task_scheduler:
  worker: "crego-task-executor"
  tasks:
    example_cleanup:
      name: "example-cleanup"
      cron: "0 2 * * *"
      should_start_immediately: false
      batch_size: 500
      retention_period: 72h
```

For environment configuration, override the same runtime fields with `TASK_SCHEDULER_WORKER`, `TASK_SCHEDULER_EXAMPLE_CLEANUP_NAME`, `TASK_SCHEDULER_EXAMPLE_CLEANUP_CRON`, `TASK_SCHEDULER_EXAMPLE_CLEANUP_SHOULD_START_IMMEDIATELY`, `TASK_SCHEDULER_EXAMPLE_CLEANUP_BATCH_SIZE`, and `TASK_SCHEDULER_EXAMPLE_CLEANUP_RETENTION_PERIOD`.

Cron expressions support standard 5-field syntax and optional 6-field syntax with seconds as the first field. When `should_start_immediately` is true, the job runs once when the scheduler starts and then follows its cron schedule.

Each generated task is registered with singleton execution, so one process will not overlap two executions of the same task. The scheduler starts during application startup and stops during graceful shutdown.

{{ if gormDistributedLock -}}
Distributed locking is enabled with `github.com/go-co-op/gocron-gorm-lock/v2` because this project uses a GORM SQL database handle. The generated scheduler auto-migrates the lock table and uses `task_scheduler.worker` as the worker identity. The lock prevents multiple compatible app instances from running the same scheduled job at the same scheduled time.
{{ else -}}
Distributed locking is not generated for this recipe. It is currently generated only when the project uses a SQL database through GORM, because that is the only generated database path with a compatible `*gorm.DB` handle.
{{ end }}

To add a new task, create a type that implements `scheduler.Task`, add its runtime config fields, construct it in `internal/app/app.go`, and register it with `taskScheduler.AddTasks(...)`. Use `internal/scheduler/tasks/example_cleanup.go` as the copyable pattern.
{{ end }}

