## Configuration
{{ if eq .Recipe.Configuration.Format "env" }}
Configuration is loaded from environment variables.

```sh
APP_ENV=development SERVER_PORT={{ .Recipe.Server.Port }} LOGGING_FORMAT={{ .Recipe.Logging.Format }}{{ if hasDatabase "postgres" }} DATABASE_POSTGRES_URL='postgres://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/app?sslmode=disable'{{ end }}{{ if hasDatabase "mysql" }} DATABASE_MYSQL_URL='mysql://root:root@tcp(localhost:3306)/app?parseTime=true'{{ end }}{{ if hasDatabase "sqlite" }} DATABASE_SQLITE_URL='file:app.db?_foreign_keys=on'{{ end }}{{ if and (anySQLDatabaseEnabled) (sqlMigrations .Recipe.Database.Migrations) }} DATABASE_MIGRATIONS='file://scripts/migrations'{{ end }}{{ if hasDatabase "redis" }} DATABASE_REDIS_ADDRESS='localhost:6379'{{ end }}{{ if hasDatabase "mongodb" }} DATABASE_MONGODB_URI='mongodb://localhost:27017/app'{{ end }} make run
```
{{ else }}
Configuration is loaded from `-config`, then `CONFIG_PATH`, then `configs/config.{{ .Recipe.Configuration.Format }}`.

Environment variables override file values:

```sh
CONFIG_PATH=configs/config.{{ .Recipe.Configuration.Format }} APP_ENV=development SERVER_PORT={{ .Recipe.Server.Port }} LOGGING_FORMAT={{ .Recipe.Logging.Format }}{{ if hasDatabase "postgres" }} DATABASE_POSTGRES_URL='postgres://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/app?sslmode=disable'{{ end }}{{ if hasDatabase "mysql" }} DATABASE_MYSQL_URL='mysql://root:root@tcp(localhost:3306)/app?parseTime=true'{{ end }}{{ if hasDatabase "sqlite" }} DATABASE_SQLITE_URL='file:app.db?_foreign_keys=on'{{ end }}{{ if and (anySQLDatabaseEnabled) (sqlMigrations .Recipe.Database.Migrations) }} DATABASE_MIGRATIONS='file://scripts/migrations'{{ end }}{{ if hasDatabase "redis" }} DATABASE_REDIS_ADDRESS='localhost:6379'{{ end }}{{ if hasDatabase "mongodb" }} DATABASE_MONGODB_URI='mongodb://localhost:27017/app'{{ end }} make run
```
{{ end }}
